                         <div style="text-align: left; margin-bottom: 10px"><a class="" data-toggle="collapse" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse-9" role="button" href="#collapse-9">Limitations on use of the premises<i class="fa fa-caret-down"></i></a>
                        <div class="collapse" id="collapse-9" style=" font-size: 12px">
                            <p class="text-justify" style="font-weight: normal;"><br>The Rental Property is to be used only as a private residence for [TENANT] and the following minor children [MINOR CHILDREN].  Occupancy by guests for more than one week is prohibited without Landlord’s written consent.<br>

Tenant, minor children identified herein, and guests or invitees, will not use the Rental Property for any illegal or nuisance activity, including, though not limited to, disturbing the peace and quiet enjoyment of the neighbors, possession or use of illegal substances, or property damage.  Tenant shall be responsible to the Landlord for the actions of Tenant’s guests and invitees. <br><br>
<strong>Note:</strong> Under some circumstances, you as a Landlord can have legal liability for criminal conduct on the premises, even if you didn’t directly cause it. Thus it is important to be aware of, and take action to stop, any illegal conduct occurring on your property.<br>

                            </p>
